Create a js file and assign one object the angular module and pass in the name of ur app: 
	In the js file you create: 
	var myApp = angular.module('myApp', []);

Tell angular what part of the view is going to be controlled by the app:
	Put the angular app directive somewhere in ur html:
	Like:
	<html ng-app="myApp">

Declare a controller in your js file, passing in a name and function: 
	myApp.controller('mainController', function() {

	});



Create a div in ur html with a controller as the attribute. Give it the name of the controller u created in the js. 
	<div ng-controller="mainController" >
	</div>



<!-- /////////////////////////========Twitter Project=======\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ -->

Create an html page with the UTF-8 charset metatag, a link element linking to ur minified bootstrap file or the CDN link and ur script elements to either a minified local file or a CDN link to anguar, jquery and ur js files in ur head element: 
	<head>
		<title>Twitter</title>
		<meta charset="UTF-8">

		<!-- load bootstrap and fontawesome via CDN (actually loading form the current directory. I downlaoded it. -) -->
		<link rel="stylesheet" href="bootstrap.min.css" />

		<!-- load angular via CDN (actually loading from the directory. I downloaded. -Kenny) -->
		<script src="angular.min.js"></script>
		<script src="twitter.js"></script>
	</head>

